<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-05-18T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-05-18T19:00:00-05:00" n="458" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d458">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/2308: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">at
                                Geneva</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-05-18T20:00:00-04:00">May 18, 1934—8
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>156. Following cable just received from Gibson at Rio de Janeiro: [Here
                            follows text of telegram No. 89, May 18, 1 p.m., from the Ambassador in
                            Brazil, printed on <ref target="#pg_358">page 358</ref>.] You may of
                            course use your discretion.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>